def landmarks(filename):
    points = 58
    X = np.zeros([2,points])
    # print(x.shape)
    
    file = open(filename)
    
    for i in range(80):
        line = file.readline()
        if (i >= 16) & (i < 16+points):
            split = line.split()
            # print(i-16)
            X[0][i-16] = float(split[2])
            X[1][i-16] = float(split[3])
    # print(X)
    return X

faces = []
for dir in listdir:
    faces.append(landmarks(dir))
    
    
X1 = landmarks('./imm_face_db/01-1m.asf')
img1 = plt.imread('./imm_face_db/01-1m.jpg')
X2 = landmarks('./imm_face_db/03-1m.asf')
img2 = plt.imread('./imm_face_db/03-1m.jpg')

height, width = img1.shape[0], img1.shape[1]

X1[0] *= width
X1[1] *= height

X2[0] *= width
X2[1] *= height

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(211)
ax1.imshow(img1)
ax1.plot(X1[0], X1[1],'.', c='r')

ax2 = fig.add_subplot(212)
ax2.imshow(img2)
ax2.plot(X2[0], X2[1], '.', c='r')

plt.show()

Average landmark compared to the face¶

In [73]:
total = []
for files in listdir:
    total.append(landmarks(files))

total = np.array(total)
total[:,0] *= width
total[:,1] *= height

mean = total.mean(axis=0).T
mean = np.append(mean, [[0,0], [0,height], [width,0],[width,height],[0,height/2], [width, height/2], [width/2, 0],[width/2, height]], axis=0)
mean = mean.T
print(mean.shape)

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(111)
ax1.imshow(img1)
ax1.plot(mean[0], mean[1],'.' , c='r')
plt.show()

Delaunay triangles on average landmarks¶

In [74]:
meantriangles = Delaunay(mean.T)


fig = plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(111)
ax1.imshow(img1)
# ax1.scatter(mean[0], mean[1], c='r')
ax1.plot(mean[0], mean[1],'.', c='r')
ax1.triplot(mean[0], mean[1], meantriangles.simplices.copy(), c='g')
plt.show()
